Subject: [PATCH 12/13] blockdev: Fix drive_del not to crash when drive is not in use

RH-Author: Markus Armbruster <armbru@redhat.com>
Message-id: <1297935168-2576-13-git-send-email-armbru@redhat.com>
Patchwork-id: 18381
O-Subject: [PATCH RHEL6.0.Z qemu-kvm 12/12] blockdev: Fix drive_del not to crash
	when drive is not in use
Bugzilla: 677170
RH-Acked-by: Marcelo Tosatti <mtosatti@redhat.com>
RH-Acked-by: Kevin Wolf <kwolf@redhat.com>
RH-Acked-by: Jes Sorensen <Jes.Sorensen@redhat.com>

Watch this:

    (qemu) drive_add 0 if=none,file=tmp.img
    OK
    (qemu) info block
    none0: type=hd removable=0 file=tmp.img ro=0 drv=raw encrypted=0
    (qemu) drive_del none0
    Segmentation fault (core dumped)

do_drive_del()'s code to clean up the pointer from a qdev using the
drive back to the drive needs to check whether such a device exists.

